{{Infobox political party |name = Israeli Druze Faction |native_name = {{Hebrew|הסיעה הדרוזית}} |lang1 = Arabic |name_lang1 = الكتلة الدرزية الإسرائيلية |lang2 = Hebrew |name_lang2 = הסיעה הדרוזית הישראלית |logo = |leader = [[Jabr Muadi]] |chairman = |president = |secretary_general = |spokesperson = |leader1_title = |leader1_name = |leader2_title = |leader2_name = |leader3_title = |leader3_name = |founded = 11 April 1967 |dissolved = 1969 |merger = |split = [[Cooperation and Brotherhood]] |merged = [[Progress and Development]] |headquarters = |newspaper = |student_wing = |youth_wing = |wing1_title = |wing1 = |wing2_title = |wing2 = |wing3_title = |wing3 = |membership_year = |membership = |ideology = Druze interest |national = |international = |europarl = |affiliation1_title = |affiliation1 = |colors = |seats1_title = Most MKs |seats1 = 1 (1967–1969) |seats2_title = Fewest MKs |seats2 = 1 (1967–1969) |symbol = |website = |country = Israel }}
The '''Israeli Druze Faction''' ({{lang-ar|الكتلة الدرزية الإسرائيلية}}, ''al-Ketla al-Druzia al-Isra'iliah'', {{lang-he|הסיעה הדרוזית הישראלית}}, ''HaSia'a HaDruzit HaYisraelit'', also labelled as the 'Druze Party') was a short-lived, one-man [[List of political parties in Israel|political faction]] in [[Israel]].
==Background== The party was established on 11 April 1967 during the [[Israeli legislative election, 1965|sixth Knesset]], when [[Jabr Muadi]] left [[Cooperation and Brotherhood]].<ref>[http://www.knesset.gov.il/faction/eng/FactionHistoryAll_eng.asp Mergers and Splits Among Parliamentary Groups] Knesset website</ref>
Before the [[Israeli legislative election, 1969|1969 elections]], Muadi joined [[Progress and Development]], thus effectively swapping parties with [[Elias Nakhleh]], who had begun the session as a member of Progress and Development, then left to set up the [[Jewish–Arab Brotherhood]] before joining Cooperation and Brotherhood.
